definition.value: A fluoroindole that is 6-fluoroindole in which the hydrogen at position 3 has been replaced by a 2-(pyridin-3-yl)vinyl group (trans configuration). It is a selective inhibitor of tryptophan 2,3-dioxygenase (TDO), which directs the conversion of trypophan to kynurenin.

A member of the class of N-nitrosoureas that is ethyl diethylphosphonate in the hydrogen at position 1 of the ethyl group attached to the phosphorus has been replaced by a [(2-chloroethyl)(nitroso)carbamoyl]amino group.
A diethyl (1-{[(2-chloroethyl)(nitroso)carbamoyl]amino}ethyl)phosphonate that has R configuration.
A diethyl (1-{[(2-chloroethyl)(nitroso)carbamoyl]amino}ethyl)phosphonate that has S configuration.
A tetracyclic meroterpenoid that is isolated from Aspergillus terreus.
A dihydroxybenzoate that is the conjugate base of 3,5-dimethylorsellinic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

An oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the a dianion resulting from the carboxy group and the beta-keto-enol group of 3-farnesyl-6-hydroxy-2,3,5-trimethyl-4-oxocyclohexa-1,5-diene-1-carboxylic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
An icosanoid anion arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function of any hydroxyicosatetraenoic acid.
An icosanoid anion arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function of any oxoicosatetraenoic acid.
An unsaturated fatty acid anion obtained by the deprotonation of the carboxy group of any octadecanoid.
An unsaturated fatty acid anion obtained by the deprotonation of the carboxy group of any hydroxyoctadecadienoic acid.
An octadecanoid anion anion obtained by the deprotonation of the carboxy group of any hydroperoxyoctadecadienoic acid.
Any oxygenated derivative of C22 polyunsaturated fatty acids, such as docosapentaenoic acid (DPA) and docosahexaenoic acid (DHA).
A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion obtained by the deprotonation of the carboxy group of any docosanoid.
An icosanoid anion obtained by the deprotonation of the carboxy group of any epoxyicosatrienoic acid.
A dihydroxyflavone that is tricin 4'-O-(erythro-beta-guaiacylglyceryl) ether in which the hydroxy hydrogen at position 7 has been replaced by a beta-D-glucopyranosyl group.
A hydroxy polyunsaturated fatty acid anion obtained by the deprotonation of the carboxy group of any hydroxydocosahexaenoic acid.
A docosanoid anion arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function of any hydroperoxydocosahexaenoic acid.
Any monounsaturated fatty acid carrying one or more hydroxy substituents.
Any monounsaturated fatty acid anion carrying one or more hydroxy substituents.
Any polyunsaturated fatty acid anion carrying one or more hydroxy substituents.
Any saturated fatty acid anion carrying one or more hydroxy substituents.
An unsaturated fatty acid anion arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function of any epoxyicosatetraenoic acid.
An unsaturated fatty acid anion arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function of any hydroxyicosapentaenoic acid (HEPE).
An icosanoid anion arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function of any hydroperoxyicosatrienoic acid.
An icosanoid anion arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function of any hydroperoxyicosapentaenoic acid.
An unsaturated fatty acid anion arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function of any dihydroxyicosatetraenoic acid.
Any steroid acid anion based on a cholanic acid skeleton.
An organic anion obtained by deprotonation of any cholanic acid conjugate.

A ketoxime that is the oxime of indan-1-one in which the hydrogen at position 5 has been replaced by an imidazol-5-yl group which has itself been substituted at positions 2 and 4 by p-[2-(dimethylamino)ethoxy]phenyl and pyridin-4-yl groups, respectively.
An N-{5-[2-{4-[2-(dimethylamino)ethoxy]phenyl}-4-(pyridin-4-yl)-1H-imidazol-5-yl]-2,3-dihydro-1H-inden-1-ylidene}hydroxylamine in which the oxime group has E configuration.
A mixture of (E)- and (Z)-SB-590885.

A trisaccharide derivative consisting of an alpha-D-glucosyl residue glycosidically linked to a 5-aminopentyl group and which carries at O-4 an alpha-L-rhamnosyl-(1->3)-beta-D-glucosyl disaccharide unit.

A 27-membered polypeptide comprising the sequence Ac-Asp-Pro-Met-Ser-Ser-Thr-Tyr-Ile-Glu-Glu-Leu-Gly-Lys-Arg-Glu-Val-Thr-Ile-Pro-Pro-Lys-Tyr-Arg-Glu-Leu-Leu-Ala-NH2. An acetylated synthetic peptide from human calpastatin that strongly inhibits both calpains I and II but not papain (a cysteine protease) or trypsin (a serine protease).
A disaccharide derivative consisting of a beta-D-glucosyl residue glycosidically linked to a 5-aminopentyl group and which carries at O-3 an alpha-L-rhamnosyl residue.
An O-acylcarnitine in which the acyl group is specified as pentadecanoyl.
An O-acylcarnitine in which the acyl group is specified as heptadecanoyl.
A prostanoid that is prostaglandin E2 having inverted stereochemistry at the 8-position.
A HEPE that consists of (5Z,8Z,12E,14Z,17Z)-icosapentaenoic acid in which the hydroxy group is located at position 11.
A glycoside that is alpha-L-rhamnose in which the hydrogen of the anomeric hydroxy group is replaced by a 5-aminopentyl group.
A disaccharide derivative consisting of an alpha-D-glucosyl residue glycosidically linked to a 5-aminopentyl group and which carries at O-2 a further alpha-D-glucosyl residue.

A trisaccharide derivative consisting of an alpha-D-glucosyl residue glycosidically linked to a 5-aminopentyl group and which carries at O-2 a beta-D-glucosyl-(1->4)-alpha-D-glucosyl disaccharide unit.

A branched tetrasaccharide derivative consisting of an alpha-D-mannosyl residue glycosidically linked to a 5-aminopentyl group and which carries at O-2 an alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl disaccharide unit and at O-4 a beta-D-galactosyl residue.
An inorganic nanoparticle consisting of cobalt cations and phosphide(3-) anions. Depending on the method of preparation, the formula can vary from CoP through Co3P2 to Co2P.
A nanoparticle consisting of graphite.
A nanoparticle consisting of tungsten atoms.
A bimetallic nanoparticle consisting of platinum and copper atoms.
A monocarboxylic acid anion resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of (R)-imazamox.
Any organic heterobicyclic compound containing two ortho-fused pyran rings.
